#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2096
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom Highlighting Text Styles"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2098
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can establish text styles for a specific syntax highlighting "
"definition, overriding the <userinput>default text style</userinput> "
"described in <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">the previous "
"section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; theme file</link>, this "
"corresponds to the <userinput>custom-styles</userinput> key, whose value is "
"an <emphasis>object</emphasis> where each subschema key corresponds to the "
"<userinput>name of a syntax highlighting definition</userinput>. Its value "
"is an <emphasis>object</emphasis> where each key refers to the "
"<userinput>style attributes name</userinput> defined in <link linkend=\"kate-"
"highlight-sections\">the <userinput>itemData</userinput> elements</link> of "
"the syntax highlighting &XML; file, and the respective value is a sub-object "
"with the keys <emphasis>text-color</emphasis>, <emphasis>selected-text-"
"color</emphasis>, <emphasis>bold</emphasis>, <emphasis>italic</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>underline</emphasis>, <emphasis>strike-through</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>background-color</emphasis> and <emphasis>selected-background-"
"color</emphasis>, defined in <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">the "
"previous section</link>. Each of these values are optional, since if they "
"are not present, the style set in <userinput>text-styles</userinput> is "
"considered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, in this piece of code, the <quote>ISO C++</quote> syntax "
"highlighting definition has a special text style for the <quote>Type "
"Modifiers</quote> and <quote>Standard Classes</quote> attributes. In the "
"corresponding &XML; file <quote>isocpp.xml</quote>, the defined attribute "
"<quote>Standard Classes</quote> uses the default style <userinput>BuiltIn</"
"userinput> (or dsBuiltIn). In this attribute, only the value of "
"<userinput>text-color</userinput> is overwritten by the new color "
"<quote>#6431b3</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:2124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\"custom-styles\": {\n"
"    \"ISO C++\": {\n"
"        \"Standard Classes\": {\n"
"            \"text-color\": \"#6431b3\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"Type Modifiers\": {\n"
"            \"bold\": true,\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\": \"#009183\",\n"
"            \"text-color\": \"#00b5cf\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should consider that these text styles are associated with the attribute "
"names defined in the syntax highlighting &XML; files. If an XML file is "
"updated and some attributes are renamed or removed, the custom style defined "
"in the theme will no longer apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Syntax highlighting definitions often include other definitions. For "
"example, the <quote>QML</quote> highlighter includes the <quote>JavaScript</"
"quote> highlighter, since they share functionality in highlighting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <link linkend=\"color-themes-gui\">the &GUI; to manage themes of "
"KTextEditor</link>, these attributes can be modified in the "
"<userinput><guilabel>Highlighting Text Styles</guilabel></userinput> tab. By "
"default, the editor preselects the highlighting of the current document. You "
"will notice that many highlights contain other highlights represented by "
"groups in the style list. For example most highlights import the "
"<quote>Alert</quote> highlight, and many source code formats import the "
"<quote>Doxygen</quote> highlight."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2159
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Color Themes &GUI;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The simplest way to create and edit color themes is through the &GUI; within "
"the <link linkend=\"config-dialog\"><quote>Configure</quote> dialog</link> "
"provided by <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/ktexteditor/html/"
"\">KTextEditor</ulink>. To access it, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Configure <replaceable>Application</replaceable>...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the menubar in your text editor. This brings "
"up the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> dialog box, there select "
"<guilabel>Color Themes</guilabel> in the side panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:2172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>&kate;'s settings dialog box with the color theme management.</"
"phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>&kate;'s settings dialog box with the color theme management.</para>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this <link linkend=\"config-dialog\">dialog</link> you can configure all "
"the colors in any theme you have, as well as create/copy new themes, delete "
"them, export them to a <userinput>.theme</userinput> file with <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; format</link> or import them from external "
"<userinput>.theme</userinput> files. Each theme has settings for text colors "
"and styles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The built-in themes cannot be modified by default. To do this, you need to "
"copy them and give them a new name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a theme permanently in your text editor, you must select it in the "
"combobox labeled <guilabel>Default theme for <replaceable>Application</"
"replaceable></guilabel> at the bottom of the dialog and press "
"<guibutton>Apply</guibutton> or <guibutton>OK</guibutton>. By default, the "
"<userinput><guilabel>Automatic Selection</guilabel></userinput> option is "
"active, which chooses a more appropriate color theme according to the "
"<emphasis>&kde; &plasma; color scheme</emphasis> used in the text editing "
"application; it usually chooses between <quote>Breeze Light</quote> and "
"<quote>Breeze Dark</quote> if the scheme is light or dark, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can adjust the &kde; global color scheme in the <ulink url=\"help:/"
"kcontrol/colors/\"><quote>Colors</quote> module in &systemsettings;</ulink>. "
"You can also change it in some applications individually such as &kate; or "
"&kdevelop;, from the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Color Scheme</guisubmenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new theme"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new theme, it is first necessary to copy an existing one. Select "
"an existing theme which you want to use as a base, such as <quote>Breeze "
"Light</quote> or <quote>Breeze Dark</quote>, and click <guibutton>Copy</"
"guibutton>. Then write a name for the new theme."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to modify a built-in or read-only theme, you must first copy it "
"under a different name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2221
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import or export &JSON; theme files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can export a selected theme (including built-in ones) to a <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link> with <userinput>.theme</userinput> "
"extension, with the <guibutton>Export</guibutton> button. This will open a "
"dialog to save the file. To add a color theme from an external <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link>, just press the <guibutton>Import</"
"guibutton> button and select the <userinput>.theme</userinput> file from the "
"dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As <link linkend=\"color-themes-json-overview\">mentioned above</link>, user-"
"customized theme files are stored in the <filename class=\"directory\">org."
"kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename> directory. When you copy or "
"create a theme, it will automatically appear there. Also, importing or "
"adding a theme is equivalent to copying an external <userinput>.theme</"
"userinput> file into this directory. KSyntaxHighlighting automatically picks "
"up color theme files from this directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to publish a theme created by you, it is essential to check the "
"<link linkend=\"color-themes-json-metadata\">metadata</link> object of the "
"<link linkend=\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link>, adding the "
"respective license and checking the revision number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2257
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing color themes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Colors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here the colors of the text editing area are adjusted. These are detailed in "
"<xref linkend=\"color-themes-editor-colors\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2276 development.docbook:2296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name in the list of styles is using the style configured for the item, "
"providing you with an immediate preview when configuring a style."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each style lets you select common attributes as well as foreground and "
"background colors. To unset a background color, right-click to use the "
"context menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The attributes of this area are detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-"
"text-styles\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2289
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Highlight Detection Rules"
msgid "Highlighting Text Styles"
msgstr "Esiletõstu tuvastamise reeglid"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can edit the text styles used by a specific highlight definition. "
"The editor preselects the highlight used by your current document. To work "
"on a different highlight, select one in the <guilabel>Highlight</guilabel> "
"combobox above the style list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each style lets you select common attributes as well as foreground and "
"background colors. To unset a background color, right-click to use the "
"context menu. In addition you can see if a style is equal to the default "
"style used for the item, and set it to that if not."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will notice that many highlights contain other highlights represented by "
"groups in the style list. For example most highlights import the Alert "
"highlight, and many source code formats imports the Doxygen highlight. "
"Editing colors in those groups only affects the styles when used in the "
"edited highlight format."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contrast of Text Colors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An important aspect when working with color themes is to choose a text "
"contrast that makes it easier to read, especially in combination with the "
"background."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>Kontrast</userinput> application is a color contrast checker. "
"It tells you that the text color and background color combinations are "
"readable and accessible, so this is an excellent tool to help you create "
"color themes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can download <userinput>Kontrast</userinput> from <ulink url=\"https://"
"apps.kde.org/en/kontrast\">the &kde; Applications website</ulink> or from "
"<ulink url=\"https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.kde.kontrast\">the Flatpak "
"package on Flathub</ulink> (only in GNU/Linux)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The GNOME <userinput>Contrast</userinput> application is similar. You can "
"download <ulink url=\"https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.gnome.design."
"Contrast\">the Flatpak package on Flathub</ulink> (only in GNU/Linux)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A python script in <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-"
"highlighting/-/blob/master/utils/theme_contrast_checker.py?ref_type=heads"
"\">Syntax Highlighting repository</ulink> lets you visualize all the colors "
"in a theme, as well as the contrast with the various backgrounds configured."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2348
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Working with Syntax Highlighting"
msgid "Suggestions of Consistency with Syntax Highlighting"
msgstr "Süntaksi esiletõstmise kasutamine"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KSyntaxHighlighting includes <ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/syntax/"
"\">more than 300 syntax highlighting definitions</ulink>, therefore it is "
"ideal that you make sure your new theme looks good in all syntax "
"highlighting definitions. The built-in color themes have the following "
"similarities that it is recommended (but not required) to follow to achieve "
"a correct display of all syntax highlighting definitions:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use bold for the <quote>Keyword</quote> and <quote>ControlFlow</quote> <link "
"linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">text styles</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not use background color in any <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles"
"\">text style</link>, except <quote>Alert</quote> and <quote>RegionMarker</"
"quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of the syntax highlighters are intended to look good on the default "
"themes <quote>Breeze Light</quote> and <quote>Breeze Dark</quote>, "
"therefore, another way to maintain consistency is to use similar colors in "
"the <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">text styles</link>, like "
"<emphasis>green</emphasis> for <quote>Preprocessor</quote> and "
"<quote>Others</quote>, <emphasis>blue</emphasis> for <quote>DataType</quote> "
"and <quote>Attribute</quote>, or <emphasis>purple</emphasis> for "
"<quote>Function</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that these recommendations are not mandatory when creating and "
"publishing a theme."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2385
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Scripting with JavaScript"
msgid "Scripting with &javascript;"
msgstr "Skriptid JavaScriptiga"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2387
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The &kappname; editor component is easily extensible by writing scripts. "
#| "The scripting language is ECMAScript (widely known as JavaScript). "
#| "&kappname; supports two kinds of scripts: indentation and command line "
#| "scripts."
msgid ""
"The &kappname; editor component is easily extensible by writing scripts. The "
"scripting language is ECMAScript (widely known as &javascript;). &kappname; "
"supports two kinds of scripts: indentation and command line scripts. A "
"functionality similar to command line scripts is also provided in the <ulink "
"url=\"help:/kate/kate-application-plugin-snippets.html\">snippets plugin</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"&kappname; redaktorikomponenti saab hõlpsalt laiendada skriptidega. "
"Skriptikeeleks on ECMAScript (rohkem tuntud kui JavaScript). &kappname; "
"toetab kaht laadi skripte: taande- ja käsureaskriptid."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indentation Scripts"
msgstr "Taandeskriptid"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Indentation scripts - also referred as indenters - automatically indent the "
"source code while typing text. As an example, after hitting the return key "
"the indentation level often increases."
msgstr ""
"Taandeskriptid või ka treppimisskriptid annavad lähtekoodile selle "
"kirjutamise ajal automaatselt vajaliku taande. Näiteks Enter-klahvi "
"vajutades taandetase tihtipeale suureneb."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following sections describe step by step how to create the skeleton for "
"a simple indenter. As a first step, create a new <filename>*.js</filename> "
"file called &eg; <filename>javascript.js</filename> in the local home folder "
"<filename>$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</"
"filename>. Therein, the environment variable <envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar> "
"typically expands to either <filename>~/.local</filename> or <filename>~/."
"local/share</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Järgnevates sektsioonides kirjeldame samm-sammult lihtsa taandeskripti "
"loomist. Kõigepealt loo uus <filename>*.js</filename>-fail, näiteks  "
"<filename>javascript.js</filename> oma kohalikus kodukataloogi kataloogis "
"<filename>$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</"
"filename>. Keskkonnamuutuja <envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar> vaste on tavaliselt "
"<filename>~/.local</filename> või <filename>~/.local/share</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2412 development.docbook:2502
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
#| "\\katepart5\\indentation</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> "
#| "usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>user</"
#| "replaceable></filename>."
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USERPROFILE%\\AppData"
"\\Local\\katepart5\\script\\indentation</filename>. <replaceable>%USERPROFILE"
"%</replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\"
"\\<replaceable>user</replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""
"&Windows; puhul asuvad need failid asukohas <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
"\\katepart5\\indentation</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> "
"tähistab tavaliselt asukohta <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>kasutaja</"
"replaceable></filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2416
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Indentation Script Header"
msgstr "Taandeskripti päis"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2417
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The header of the file <filename>javascript.js</filename> is embedded as "
#| "JSON at the beginning of the document as follows: <programlisting>\n"
#| "var katescript = {\n"
#| "    \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n"
#| "    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
#| "    \"license\": \"BSD License\",\n"
#| "    \"revision\": 1,\n"
#| "    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
#| "    \"required-syntax-style\": \"javascript\",\n"
#| "    \"indent-languages\": [\"javascript\"],\n"
#| "    \"priority\": 0,\n"
#| "}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without "
#| "comments\n"
#| "</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgid ""
"The header of the file <filename>javascript.js</filename> is embedded as "
"&JSON; at the beginning of the document as follows: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n"
"    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
"    \"license\": \"BSD License\",\n"
"    \"revision\": 1,\n"
"    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
"    \"required-syntax-style\": \"javascript\",\n"
"    \"indent-languages\": [\"javascript\"],\n"
"    \"priority\": 0,\n"
"}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without comments\n"
"</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgstr ""
"Faili <filename>javascript.js</filename> on päis põimitud JSON-ina dokumendi "
"algusse ning näeb välja selline: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n"
"    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
"    \"license\": \"BSD License\",\n"
"    \"revision\": 1,\n"
"    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
"    \"required-syntax-style\": \"javascript\",\n"
"    \"indent-languages\": [\"javascript\"],\n"
"    \"priority\": 0,\n"
"}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without comments\n"
"</programlisting> Allpool selgitatakse põhjalikult iga kirjet:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>name</literal> [required]: This is the indenter name that appears "
"in the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Indentation</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> and in the configuration dialog."
msgstr ""
"<literal>name</literal> [kohustuslik]: see on taandeskripti nimi, nagu seda "
"näeb menüüs <menuchoice><guimenu>Tööriistad</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Treppimine</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ja "
"seadistustedialoogis."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2429 development.docbook:2558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>author</literal> [optional]: The author's name and contact "
"information."
msgstr ""
"<literal>author</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: autori nimi ja kontaktteave."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>license</literal> [optional]: Short form of the license, such as "
"BSD License or LGPLv3."
msgstr ""
"<literal>license</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: litsents lühidalt, näiteks "
"BSD või LGPLv3."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2435 development.docbook:2560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>revision</literal> [required]: The revision of the script. This "
"number should be increased whenever the script is modified."
msgstr ""
"<literal>revision</literal> [kohustuslik]: skripti versioon. Seda arvu tuleb "
"alati suurendada, kui skripti muudetakse."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2438 development.docbook:2561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>kate-version</literal> [required]: Minimum required &kappname; "
"version."
msgstr ""
"<literal>kate-version</literal> [kohustuslik]: &kappname; minimaalne nõutav "
"versioon."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>required-syntax-style</literal> [optional]: The required syntax "
"style, which matches the specified <literal>style</literal> in syntax "
"highlighting files. This is important for indenters that rely on specific "
"highlight information in the document. If a required syntax style is "
"specified, the indenter is available only when the appropriate highlighter "
"is active. This prevents <quote>undefined behavior</quote> caused by using "
"the indenter without the expected highlighting schema. For instance, the "
"Ruby indenter makes use of this in the files <filename>ruby.js</filename> "
"and <filename>ruby.xml</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>required-syntax-style</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: nõutav süntaksi "
"stiil, mis sobib määratlusega <literal>style</literal> süntaksi "
"esiletõstmise failides. See on oluline taandeskriptide puhul, mis toetuvad "
"teatavale dokumendis leiduvale esiletõstmise teabele. Kui nõutav "
"süntaksistiil on määratud, saab taandeskripti kasutada ainult siis, kui "
"aktiivne on sobiv esiletõstmise skeem. See takistab <quote>sobimatut "
"käitumist</quote>, mis võib tekkida, kui taandeskripti kasutatakse eeldatud "
"esiletõstmise skeemita. Näiteks Ruby taandeskript kasutab sellist võimalust "
"failides <filename>ruby.js</filename> ja <filename>ruby.xml</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2444
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>indent-languages</literal> [optional]: JSON array of syntax "
#| "styles the indenter can indent correctly, &eg;: <literal>[\"c++\", \"java"
#| "\"]</literal>."
msgid ""
"<literal>indent-languages</literal> [optional]: &JSON; array of syntax "
"styles the indenter can indent correctly, &eg;: <literal>[\"c++\", \"java"
"\"]</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>indent-languages</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: süntaksistiilide "
"JSON-i massiiv, mille puhul taandeskript suudab korrektselt treppimist "
"rakendada, näiteks <literal>[\"c++\", \"java\"]</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>priority</literal> [optional]: If several indenters are suited for "
"a certain highlighted file, the priority decides which indenter is chosen as "
"default indenter."
msgstr ""
"<literal>priority</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: kui teatava esiletõstmisega "
"faili puhul sobib mitu taandeskripti, siis prioriteet määrab, millist neist "
"kasutatakse vaikimisi."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2456
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Indenter Source Code"
msgstr "Taandeskripti lähtekood"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2457
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
#| "scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
#| "<programlisting>\n"
#| "// required katepart js libraries, e.g. range.js if you use Range\n"
#| "require (\"range.js\");\n"
#| "  \n"
#| "triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
#| "function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
#| "{\n"
#| "    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
#| "in\n"
#| "    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></"
#| "menuchoice>\n"
#| "    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
#| "    //\n"
#| "    // see also: Scripting API\n"
#| "    return -2;\n"
#| "}\n"
#| "</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
#| "parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the "
#| "line that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
#| "<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
#| "number of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
#| "either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), the trigger "
#| "character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> or empty if "
#| "the user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> "
#| "</itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</function> "
#| "function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return value is "
#| "a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: <itemizedlist> "
#| "<listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do nothing</para></"
#| "listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</literal>: keep "
#| "indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></listitem> "
#| "<listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= 0 "
#| "specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> "
#| "Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: <itemizedlist> "
#| "<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
#| "listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first element is the "
#| "indentation depth as above with the same meaning of the special values. "
#| "However, the second element is an absolute value representing a column "
#| "for <quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is higher than the indent "
#| "value, the difference represents a number of spaces to be added after the "
#| "indentation of the first parameter. Otherwise, the second number is "
#| "ignored. Using tabs and spaces for indentation is often referred to as "
#| "<quote>mixed mode</quote>."
msgid ""
"Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
"scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
"<programlisting>\n"
"// required katepart js libraries, &eg; range.js if you use Range\n"
"require (\"range.js\");\n"
"\n"
"triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
"function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
"{\n"
"    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
"in\n"
"    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Format Indentation</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>\n"
"    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
"    //\n"
"    // see also: Scripting API\n"
"    return -2;\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
"parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the line "
"that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
"<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
"number of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
"either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), the trigger "
"character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> or empty if the "
"user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Format Indentation</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</"
"function> function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return "
"value is a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: "
"<itemizedlist> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do "
"nothing</para></listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</"
"literal>: keep indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></"
"listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= "
"0 specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> "
"Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first element is the indentation "
"depth as above with the same meaning of the special values. However, the "
"second element is an absolute value representing a column for "
"<quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is higher than the indent value, the "
"difference represents a number of spaces to be added after the indentation "
"of the first parameter. Otherwise, the second number is ignored. Using tabs "
"and spaces for indentation is often referred to as <quote>mixed mode</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Kui päis on defineeritud, siis siin osas saab aimu, kuidas töötab "
"taandeskript ise. Põhimõtteliselt näeb see välja nii: <programlisting>\n"
"// nõutavad katepart js teegid, nt. range.js, kui kasutad Range'i\n"
"require (\"range.js\");\n"
"  \n"
"triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
"function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
"{\n"
"    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
"in\n"
"    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>\n"
"    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
"    //\n"
"    // see also: Scripting API\n"
"    return -2;\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting> Funktsioonil <function>indent()</function> on kolm "
"parameetrit: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: rida, "
"mida asutakse treppima</para></listitem> "
"<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: treppimise ehk taande laius "
"tühimärkide arvuna</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
"kas reavahetuse sümbol (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), käivitamissümbol, "
"mille määrab kindlaks <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> või ka tühi, kui "
"kasutaja kustub välja toimingu <menuchoice><guimenu>Tööriistad</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Joondamine</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> Funktsiooni <function>indent()</function> "
"tagastatav väärtus määrab, kuidas rida trepitakse. Kui tagastatud väärtus on "
"lihtsalt täisarv, tõlgendatakse seda järgnevalt: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para>tagastatud väärtus <literal>-2</literal>: ei tehta midagi</"
"para></listitem> <listitem><para>tagastatud väärtus <literal>-1</literal>: "
"säilitatakse taandus (otsitakse eelmist mittetühja rida)</para></listitem> "
"<listitem><para>tagastatud väärtus <literal> 0</literal>: arv &gt;= 0 määrab "
"taandesügavuse tühimärkide arvuna</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> Teise "
"võimalusena tagastatakse kahest elemendist koosnev massiiv: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> Sel juhul on esimene element taandesügavus nagu "
"ülal ja samade eriväärtustega. Teine element on aga absoluutväärtus, mis "
"tähistab <quote>joonduse</quote> veergu. Kui see väärtus on suurem kui "
"taande väärtus, tähistab nende erinevus tühimärkide arvu, mis tuleb lisada "
"esimese parameetriga määratud taande järele. Muul juhul teist arvu "
"eiratakse. Tabeldusmärkide ja tühimärkide kasutamist treppimisel nimetatakse "
"sageli <quote>segarežiimiks</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider the following example: Assume using tabs to indent, and tab width "
"is set to 4. Here, &lt;tab&gt; represents a tab and '.' a space: "
"<programlisting>\n"
"1: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;foobar(\"hello\",\n"
"2: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;.......\"world\");\n"
"</programlisting> When indenting line 2, the <function>indent()</function> "
"function returns [8, 15]. As result, two tabs are inserted to indent to "
"column 8, and 7 spaces are added to align the second parameter under the "
"first, so that it stays aligned if the file is viewed with a different tab "
"width."
msgstr ""
"Vaatame järgmist näidet. Eeldame, et treppimiseks kasutatakse tabeldusmärke "
"ning nende laiuseks on määratud 4. &lt;tab&gt; tähistab tabeldusmärki ja '.' "
"tühimärki: <programlisting>\n"
"1: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;foobar(\"hello\",\n"
"2: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;.......\"world\");\n"
"</programlisting> Teise taandega rea puhul tagastab funktsioon "
"<function>indent()</function> [8, 15]. Seepärast lisatakse kaks "
"tabeldusmärki veeru 8 treppimiseks ning 7 tühimärki teise parameetri "
"joondamiseks esimese alla, et see oleks joondatud ka siis, kui faili "
"vaadatakse mõne muu tabeldusmärgi laiusega."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2499
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A default &kde; installation ships &kappname; with several indenters. The "
#| "corresponding JavaScript source code can be found in <filename>"
#| "$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</filename>."
msgid ""
"A default &kde; installation ships &kappname; with several indenters. The "
"corresponding &javascript; source code can be found in <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</filename>."
msgstr ""
"&kde; vaikimisi paigalduse puhul pakub &kappname; mitut taandeskripti. "
"Vastava JavaScripti lähtekoodi leiab kataloogist <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Developing an indenter requires reloading the scripts to see whether the "
"changes behave appropriately. Instead of restarting the application, simply "
"switch to the command line and invoke the command <command>reload-scripts</"
"command>."
msgstr ""
"Taandeskripti arendamiseks tuleb skriptid taaslaadida, et näha, kas "
"muudatused, mida nad teevad, on korrektsed. Terve rakenduse taaskäivitamise "
"asemel lülitu lihtsalt käsureale ja anna käsk <command>reload-scripts</"
"command>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2512 development.docbook:2624
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you develop useful scripts please consider contributing to the "
#| "&kappname; Project by <ulink url=\"mailto:kwrite-devel@kde.org"
#| "\">contacting the mailing list</ulink>."
msgid ""
"If you develop useful scripts please consider contributing to the &kappname; "
"Project by providing a merge request to <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/"
"frameworks/ktexteditor\">our GitLab project</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Kui lood mõne kasuliku skripti, võiksid kaaluda selle annetamist ka "
"&kappname; hüvanguks. Selleks võib ühendust võtta <ulink url=\"mailto:kwrite-"
"devel@kde.org\">postiloendis</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2521
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Scripts"
msgstr "Käsureaskriptid"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A functionality similar to command line scripts is also provided in the "
"<ulink url=\"help:/kate/kate-application-plugin-snippets.html\">snippets "
"plugin</ulink>. This plugin may provide an easier starting point, especially "
"for small custom scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As it is hard to satisfy everyone's needs, &kappname; supports little helper "
"tools for quick text manipulation through the <link linkend=\"advanced-"
"editing-tools-commandline\">built-in command line</link>. For instance, the "
"command <command>sort</command> is implemented as a script. This section "
"explains how to create <filename>*.js</filename> files to extend &kappname; "
"with arbitrary helper scripts."
msgstr ""
"Et kõigi vajadusi on ühekorraga raske rahuldada, toetab &kappname; pisikesi "
"abitööriistu teksti kiireks töötlemiseks <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-"
"tools-commandline\">sisseehitatud käsurea abil</link>. Näiteks käsk "
"<command>sort</command> on teostatud skriptina. Järgnevas osas selgitatakse, "
"kuidas luua <filename>*.js</filename>-faile &kappname; laiendamiseks mis "
"tahes abiskriptidega."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Command line scripts are located in the same folder as indentation scripts. "
"So as a first step, create a new <filename>*.js</filename> file called "
"<filename>myutils.js</filename> in the local home folder <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/script/commands</filename>. Therein, "
"the environment variable <envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar> typically expands to "
"either <filename>~/.local</filename> or <filename>~/.local/share</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Käsureaskriptid paiknevad samas kataloogis taandeskriptidega. Niisiis, "
"esimese sammuna loo uus <filename>*.js</filename>-fail nimega "
"<filename>myutils.js</filename> kohalikus kodukataloogis <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/script/commands</filename>. "
"Keskkonnamuutuja <envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar> vaste on tavaliselt "
"<filename>~/.local</filename> või <filename>~/.local/share</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2545
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
#| "\\katepart5\\commands</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> "
#| "usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>user</"
#| "replaceable></filename>."
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USERPROFILE%\\AppData"
"\\Local\\katepart5\\script\\commands</filename>. <replaceable>%USERPROFILE%</"
"replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>user</"
"replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""
"&Windows; puhul asuvad need failid asukohas <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
"\\katepart5\\commands</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> tähistab "
"tavaliselt asukohta <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>kasutaja</"
"replaceable></filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2550
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Command Line Script Header"
msgstr "Käsureaskripti päis"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2551
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The header of each command line script is embedded in JSON at the "
#| "beginning of the script as follows: <programlisting>\n"
#| "var katescript = {\n"
#| "    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
#| "    \"license\": \"LGPLv2+\",\n"
#| "    \"revision\": 1,\n"
#| "    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
#| "    \"functions\": [\"sort\", \"moveLinesDown\"],\n"
#| "    \"actions\": [\n"
#| "        {   \"function\": \"sort\",\n"
#| "            \"name\": \"Sort Selected Text\",\n"
#| "            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
#| "            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
#| "        },\n"
#| "        {   \"function\": \"moveLinesDown\",\n"
#| "            \"name\": \"Move Lines Down\",\n"
#| "            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
#| "            \"shortcut\": \"Ctrl+Shift+Down\",\n"
#| "            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
#| "        }\n"
#| "    ]\n"
#| "}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without "
#| "comments\n"
#| "</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgid ""
"The header of each command line script is embedded in &JSON; at the "
"beginning of the script as follows: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
"    \"license\": \"LGPLv2+\",\n"
"    \"revision\": 1,\n"
"    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
"    \"functions\": [\"sort\", \"moveLinesDown\"],\n"
"    \"actions\": [\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"sort\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Sort Selected Text\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"moveLinesDown\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Move Lines Down\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"shortcut\": \"Ctrl+Shift+Down\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    ]\n"
"}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without comments\n"
"</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgstr ""
"Kõigi käsureaskriptide päis on põimitud JSON-ina skripti algusse ning näeb "
"välja selline: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
"    \"license\": \"LGPLv2+\",\n"
"    \"revision\": 1,\n"
"    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
"    \"functions\": [\"sort\", \"moveLinesDown\"],\n"
"    \"actions\": [\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"sort\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Sort Selected Text\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"moveLinesDown\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Move Lines Down\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"shortcut\": \"Ctrl+Shift+Down\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    ]\n"
"}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without comments\n"
"</programlisting> Allpool selgitatakse põhjalikult iga kirjet:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>license</literal> [optional]: Short form of the license, such as "
"BSD License or LGPLv2."
msgstr ""
"<literal>license</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: litsents lühidalt, näiteks "
"BSD või LGPLv2."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2562
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>functions</literal> [required]: JSON array of commands in the "
#| "script."
msgid ""
"<literal>functions</literal> [required]: &JSON; array of commands in the "
"script."
msgstr ""
"<literal>functions</literal> [kohustuslik]: skripti käskude JSON-i massiiv."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2563
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>actions</literal> [optional]: JSON Array of JSON objects that "
#| "defines the actions that appear in the application menu. Detailed "
#| "information is provided in the section <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-"
#| "tools-commandline\">Binding Shortcuts</link>."
msgid ""
"<literal>actions</literal> [optional]: &JSON; Array of &JSON; objects that "
"defines the actions that appear in the application menu. Detailed "
"information is provided in the section <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-"
"tools-commandline\">Binding Shortcuts</link>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>actions</literal> [optional]: JSON-i objektide JSONi massiiv, mis "
"määratleb rakenduse menüüs näha olevad toimingud. Täpsemalt kõneldakse "
"sellest osas <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-tools-commandline"
"\">Kiirklahvid</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2567
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Since the value of <literal>functions</literal> is a JSON array, a single "
#| "script is able to contain an arbitrary number of command line commands. "
#| "Each function is available through &kappname;'s <link linkend=\"advanced-"
#| "editing-tools-commandline\">built-in command line</link>."
msgid ""
"Since the value of <literal>functions</literal> is a &JSON; array, a single "
"script is able to contain an arbitrary number of command line commands. Each "
"function is available through &kappname;'s <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-"
"tools-commandline\">built-in command line</link>."
msgstr ""
"Et <literal>functions</literal> väärtus on JSON-i massiiv, võib üksainus "
"skript sisaldada suvalisel hulgal käsurea käske. Kõik funktsioonid on "
"saadaval &kappname;i <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-tools-commandline"
"\">sisseehitatud käsurea</link> vahendusel."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2575
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Script Source Code"
msgstr "Skripti lähtekood"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All functions specified in the header have to be implemented in the script. "
"For instance, the script file from the example above needs to implement the "
"two functions <command>sort</command> and <command>moveLinesDown</command>. "
"All functions have the following syntax:"
msgstr ""
"Kõik päises osutatud funktsioonid tuleb skriptis teostada. Nii peab näiteks "
"ülaltoodud näites esitatud skript teostama kaks funktsiooni: <command>sort</"
"command> ja <command>moveLinesDown</command>. Kõigil funktsioonidel on "
"järgmine süntaks:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:2583
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "// required katepart js libraries, e.g. range.js if you use Range\n"
#| "require (\"range.js\");\n"
#| "\n"
#| "function &lt;name&gt;(arg1, arg2, ...)\n"
#| "{\n"
#| "    // ... implementation, see also: Scripting API\n"
#| "}"
msgid ""
"// required katepart js libraries, &eg; range.js if you use Range\n"
"require (\"range.js\");\n"
"\n"
"function &lt;name&gt;(arg1, arg2, ...)\n"
"{\n"
"    // ... implementation, see also: Scripting API\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"// nõutavad katepart js teegid, nt. range.js, kui kasutad Range'i\n"
"require (\"range.js\");\n"
"\n"
"function &lt;nimi&gt;(arg1, arg2, ...)\n"
"{\n"
"    // ... implementation, see also: Scripting API\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2586
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Arguments in the command line are passed to the function as "
#| "<parameter>arg1</parameter>, <parameter>arg2</parameter>, etc. In order "
#| "to provide documentation for each command, simply implement the "
#| "'<function>help</function>' function as follows: <programlisting>\n"
#| "function help(cmd)\n"
#| "{\n"
#| "    if (cmd == \"sort\") {\n"
#| "        return i18n(\"Sort the selected text.\");\n"
#| "    } else if (cmd == \"...\") {\n"
#| "        // ...\n"
#| "    }\n"
#| "}\n"
#| "</programlisting> Executing <command>help sort</command> in the command "
#| "line then calls this help function with the argument <parameter>cmd</"
#| "parameter> set to the given command, &ie; <parameter>cmd == \"sort\"</"
#| "parameter>. &kappname; then presents the returned text as documentation "
#| "to the user. Make sure to <link linkend=\"dev-scripting-api-i18n"
#| "\">translate the strings</link>."
msgid ""
"Arguments in the command line are passed to the function as <parameter>arg1</"
"parameter>, <parameter>arg2</parameter>, &etc; In order to provide "
"documentation for each command, simply implement the '<function>help</"
"function>' function as follows: <programlisting>\n"
"function help(cmd)\n"
"{\n"
"    if (cmd == \"sort\") {\n"
"        return i18n(\"Sort the selected text.\");\n"
"    } else if (cmd == \"...\") {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting> Executing <command>help sort</command> in the command line "
"then calls this help function with the argument <parameter>cmd</parameter> "
"set to the given command, &ie; <parameter>cmd == \"sort\"</parameter>. "
"&kappname; then presents the returned text as documentation to the user. "
"Make sure to <link linkend=\"dev-scripting-api-i18n\">translate the strings</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Argumendid edastatakse käsureal funktsioonile kujul <parameter>arg1</"
"parameter>, <parameter>arg2</parameter> jne. Kõigi käskude kohta "
"dokumentatsiooni pakkumiseks teosta lihtsalt funktsioon  '<function>help</"
"function>': <programlisting>\n"
"function help(cmd)\n"
"{\n"
"    if (cmd == \"sort\") {\n"
"        return i18n(\"Sort the selected text.\");\n"
"    } else if (cmd == \"...\") {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting> Käsureal <command>help sort</command> käivitamine kutsub "
"välja abifunktsiooni argumendiga <parameter>cmd</parameter>, mille "
"väärtuseks on määratud antud käsk, s.t <parameter>cmd == \"sort\"</"
"parameter>. &kappname; tagastab seejärel teksti kasutajale nähtava "
"dokumentatsioonina. Kontrolli kindlasti, et ikka <link linkend=\"dev-"
"scripting-api-i18n\">tõlgid stringid</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Developing a command line script requires reloading the scripts to see "
"whether the changes behave appropriately. Instead of restarting the "
"application, simply switch to the command line and invoke the command "
"<command>reload-scripts</command>."
msgstr ""
"Käsureaskripti arendamiseks tuleb skriptid taaslaadida, et näha, kas "
"muudatused, mida nad teevad, on korrektsed. Terve rakenduse taaskäivitamise "
"asemel lülitu lihtsalt käsureale ja anna käsk <command>reload-scripts</"
"command>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2608
#, no-c-format
msgid "Binding Shortcuts"
msgstr "Kiirklahvid"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2609
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to make the scripts accessible in the application menu and assign "
"shortcuts, the script needs to provide an appropriate script header. In the "
"above example, both functions <literal>sort</literal> and "
"<literal>moveLinesDown</literal> appear in the menu due to the following "
"part in the script header: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    ...\n"
"    \"actions\": [\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"sort\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Sort Selected Text\",\n"
"            \"icon\": \"\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"moveLinesDown\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Move Lines Down\",\n"
"            \"icon\": \"\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"shortcut\": \"Ctrl+Shift+Down\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    ]\n"
"};\n"
"</programlisting> The fields for one action are as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Et skriptid oleksid kättesaadavad rakenduse menüüs ja neil oleksid ka "
"kiirklahvid, peab skript pakkuma sobiliku skriptipäise. Siinses näites on "
"nii funktsioon <literal>sort</literal> kui ka <literal>moveLinesDown</"
"literal> menüüs näha järgmise skriptipäise osa tõttu: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    ...\n"
"    \"actions\": [\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"sort\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Sort Selected Text\",\n"
"            \"icon\": \"\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {   \"function\": \"moveLinesDown\",\n"
"            \"name\": \"Move Lines Down\",\n"
"            \"icon\": \"\",\n"
"            \"category\": \"Editing\",\n"
"            \"shortcut\": \"Ctrl+Shift+Down\",\n"
"            \"interactive\": \"false\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    ]\n"
"};\n"
"</programlisting> Toimingu väljad on järgmised:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>function</literal> [required]: The function that should appear in "
"the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Scripts</"
"guisubmenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>function</literal> [kohustuslik]: funktsioon, mida näeb menüüs "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tööriistad</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Skriptid</guisubmenu></"
"menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>name</literal> [required]: The text appears in the script menu."
msgstr "<literal>name</literal> [kohustuslik]: tekst, mida näeb skriptimenüüs."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>icon</literal> [optional]: The icon appears next to the text in the "
"menu. All &kde; icon names can be used here."
msgstr ""
"<literal>icon</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: ikoon, mida näeb menüüs teksti "
"kõrval. Siin võib kasutada kõiki &kde; ikooninimesid."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>category</literal> [optional]: If a category is specified, the "
"script appears in a submenu."
msgstr ""
"<literal>category</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: kategooria määramisel näeb "
"skripti alammenüüs."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2619
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>shortcut</literal> [optional]: The shortcut given here is the "
#| "default shortcut. Example: <literal>Ctrl+Alt+t</literal>. See the <ulink "
#| "url=\"http://qt-project.org/doc/qt-5/qt.html#Key-enum\">Qt documentation</"
#| "ulink> for further details."
msgid ""
"<literal>shortcut</literal> [optional]: The shortcut given here is the "
"default shortcut. Example: <literal>Ctrl+Alt+t</literal>. See the <ulink url="
"\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qt.html#Key-enum\">&Qt; documentation</ulink> for "
"further details."
msgstr ""
"<literal>shortcut</literal> [pole kohustuslik]: siin määratud kiirklahv on "
"vaikimisi kiirklahv. Näide: <literal>Ctrl+Alt+t</literal>. Täpsemalt "
"kõneldakse sellest <ulink url=\"http://qt-project.org/doc/qt-5/qt.html#Key-"
"enum\">Qt dokumentatsioonis</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>interactive</literal> [optional]: If the script needs user input in "
"the command line, set this to <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>interactive</literal>: kui skript vajab kasutajapoolset sisendit "
"käsureal, tuleb selle väärtuseks määrata <literal>true</literal>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2634
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripting API"
msgstr "Skriptimise API"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The scripting API presented here is available to all scripts, &ie; "
"indentation scripts and command line commands. The <classname>Cursor</"
"classname> and <classname>Range</classname> classes are provided by library "
"files in <filename>$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</envar>/katepart5/libraries</"
"filename>. If you want to use them in your script, which needs to use some "
"of the <classname>Document</classname> or <classname>View</classname> "
"functions, please include the necessary library by using:"
msgstr ""
"Siinne skriptimise API on saadaval kõigis skriptides, s.t nii taande- kui ka "
"käsureaskriptides. Klasse <classname>Cursor</classname> ja <classname>Range</"
"classname> pakuvad teegifailid kataloogis <filename>$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</"
"envar>/katepart5/libraries</filename>. Kui soovid neid oma skriptis "
"kasutada, mis on nõutav mõningate klasside <classname>Document</classname> "
"või <classname>View</classname> funktsioonide kasutamiseks, kaasa palun "
"vajalik teek järgmiselt:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:2642
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "// required katepart js libraries, e.g. range.js if you use Range\n"
#| "require (\"range.js\");"
msgid ""
"// required katepart js libraries, &eg; range.js if you use Range\n"
"require (\"range.js\");"
msgstr ""
"// nõutavad katepart js teegid, nt. range.js , kui kasutad Range'i\n"
"require (\"range.js\");"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To extend the standard scripting API with your own functions and prototypes "
"simply create a new file in &kde;'s local configuration folder <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/libraries</filename> and include it "
"into your script using:"
msgstr ""
"Standardse skriptimise API laiendamiseks oma funktsioonide ja prototüüpidega "
"loo lihtsalt uus fail &kde; kohalikus seadistuste kataloogis <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/libraries</filename> ja kaasa see "
"oma skripti järgmiselt:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:2650
#, no-c-format
msgid "require (\"myscriptnamehere.js\");"
msgstr "require (\"myscriptnamehere.js\");"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2654
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
#| "\\katepart5\\libraries</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> "
#| "usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>user</"
#| "replaceable></filename>."
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USERPROFILE%\\AppData"
"\\Local\\katepart5\\libraries</filename>. <replaceable>%USERPROFILE%</"
"replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>user</"
"replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""
"&Windows; puhul asuvad need failid asukohas <filename>%USER%\\AppData\\Local"
"\\katepart5\\libraries</filename>. <replaceable>%USER%</replaceable> "
"tähistab tavaliselt asukohta <filename>C:\\\\Users\\\\<replaceable>kasutaja</"
"replaceable></filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2657
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To extend existing prototypes like <classname>Cursor</classname> or "
#| "<classname>Range</classname>, the recommended way is to <emphasis>not</"
#| "emphasis> modify the global <filename>*.js</filename> files. Instead, "
#| "change the <classname>Cursor</classname> prototype in JavaScript after "
#| "the <filename>cursor.js</filename> is included into your script via "
#| "<literal>require</literal>."
msgid ""
"To extend existing prototypes like <classname>Cursor</classname> or "
"<classname>Range</classname>, the recommended way is to <emphasis>not</"
"emphasis> modify the global <filename>*.js</filename> files. Instead, change "
"the <classname>Cursor</classname> prototype in &javascript; after the "
"<filename>cursor.js</filename> is included into your script via "
"<literal>require</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Olemasolevate prototüüpide, näiteks <classname>Cursor</classname> või "
"<classname>Range</classname>, laiendamiseks <emphasis>ei ole</emphasis> "
"soovitatav muuta globaalseid <filename>*.js</filename>-faile. Selle asemel "
"muuda prototüüpi <classname>Cursor</classname> JavaScriptis pärast seda, kui "
"<filename>cursor.js</filename> on <literal>require</literal> abil skripti "
"kaasatud."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2666
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cursors and Ranges"
msgstr "Kursorid ja vahemikud"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As &kappname; is a text editor, all the scripting API is based on cursors "
"and ranges whenever possible. A Cursor is a simple <literal>(line, column)</"
"literal> tuple representing a text position in the document. A Range spans "
"text from a starting cursor position to an ending cursor position. The API "
"is explained in detail in the next sections."
msgstr ""
"Kuna &kappname; on tekstiredaktor, siis on kogu skriptimise API aluseks, nii "
"palju kui võimalik, kursorid ja vahemikud. Kursor kujutab endast lihtsat "
"<literal>(rida,veerg)</literal> määratlust, mis näitab ära teksti asukoha "
"dokumendis. Vahemik aga paneb paika tekstivahemiku kursori algasukohast "
"selle lõppasukohani. API seletatakse üksikasjalikult lahti järgmistes "
"lõikudes."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2677
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Cursor Prototype"
msgstr "Kursori prototüüp"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2680
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cursor();"
msgstr "Cursor();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2681
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructor. Returns a Cursor at position <literal>(0, 0)</literal>."
msgstr "Konstruktor. Tagastab kursori asukohas <literal>(0, 0)</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2683
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var cursor = new Cursor();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var cursor = new Cursor();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2689
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cursor(<parameter>int <replaceable>line</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>column</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"Cursor(<parameter>int <replaceable>rida</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>veerg</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructor. Returns a Cursor at position (line, column)."
msgstr "Konstruktor. Tagastab kursori asukohas (rida, veerg)."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2693
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var cursor = new Cursor(3, 42);</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var cursor = new Cursor(3, 42);</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cursor(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"Cursor(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy constructor. Returns a copy of the cursor <replaceable>other</"
"replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Koopia konstruktor. Tagastab kursori koopia <replaceable>other</replaceable>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2703
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var copy = new Cursor(other);</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var copy = new Cursor(other);</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cursor Cursor.clone();"
msgstr "Cursor Cursor.clone();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2710
#, no-c-format
msgid "Returns a clone of the cursor."
msgstr "Tagastab kursori klooni."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var clone = cursor.clone();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var clone = cursor.clone();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2718
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cursor.setPosition(<parameter>int <replaceable>line</replaceable></"
"parameter>, <parameter>int <replaceable>column</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"Cursor.setPosition(<parameter>int <replaceable>rida</replaceable></"
"parameter>, <parameter>int <replaceable>veerg</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the cursor position to <replaceable>line</replaceable> and "
"<replaceable>column</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Määrab kursori asukoha <replaceable>rea</replaceable> ja "
"<replaceable>veeruga</replaceable>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2721 development.docbook:2833
#, no-c-format
msgid "Since: &kde; 4.11"
msgstr "Alates: &kde; 4.11"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2728
#, no-c-format
msgid "bool Cursor.isValid();"
msgstr "bool Cursor.isValid();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2729
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check whether the cursor is valid. The cursor is invalid, if line and/or "
"column are set to <literal>-1</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Kontrollib, kas kursor on korrektne. Kursor ei ole korrektne, kui rida ja/"
"või veeru väärtuseks on määratud <literal>-1</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2733
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var valid = cursor.isValid();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var valid = cursor.isValid();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cursor Cursor.invalid();"
msgstr "Cursor Cursor.invalid();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2741
#, no-c-format
msgid "Returns a new invalid cursor located at <literal>(-1, -1)</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab uue ebakorrektse kursori asukohas <literal>(-1, -1)</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2744
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var invalidCursor = cursor.invalid();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var invalidCursor = cursor.invalid();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2749
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"int Cursor.compareTo(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"int Cursor.compareTo(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Compares this cursor to the cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable>. Returns"
msgstr ""
"Võrdleb antud kursorit kursoriga <replaceable>other</replaceable>. Tagastab"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>-1</literal>, if this cursor is located before the cursor "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>,"
msgstr ""
"<literal>-1</literal>, kui antud kursor paikneb enne kursorit "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>,"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2754
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>0</literal>, if both cursors equal and"
msgstr "<literal>0</literal>, kui mõlemad kursorid on võrdsed,"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>+1</literal>, if this cursor is located after the cursor "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>-+1</literal>, kui antud kursor paikneb pärast kursorit "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2762
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"bool Cursor.equals(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"bool Cursor.equals(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2763
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if this cursor and the cursor "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable> are equal, otherwise <literal>false</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab <literal>true</literal>, kui antud kursor ja kursor "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable> on võrdsed, vastasel juhul <literal>false</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2771
#, no-c-format
msgid "String Cursor.toString();"
msgstr "String Cursor.toString();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns the cursor as a string of the form <quote><literal>Cursor(line, "
"column)</literal></quote>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab kursori stringina kujul <quote><literal>Cursor(rida, veerg)</"
"literal></quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2781
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Range Prototype"
msgstr "Vahemiku prototüüp"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2784
#, no-c-format
msgid "Range();"
msgstr "Range();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Constructor. Calling <literal>new Range()</literal> returns a Range at (0, "
"0) - (0, 0)."
msgstr ""
"Konstruktor <literal>new Range()</literal> väljakutsumine tagastab vahemiku "
"(0, 0) - (0, 0)."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Range(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>start</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>end</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"Range(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>algus</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>lõpp</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2793
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Constructor. Calling <literal>new Range(<replaceable>start</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>end</replaceable>)</literal> returns the Range "
"(<replaceable>start</replaceable>, <replaceable>end</replaceable>)."
msgstr ""
"Konstruktor <literal>new Range(<replaceable>algus</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>lõpp</replaceable>)</literal> väljakutsumine tagastab vahemiku "
"(<replaceable>algus</replaceable>, <replaceable>lõpp</replaceable>)."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2800
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Range(<parameter>int <replaceable>startLine</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>startColumn</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>endLine</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>endColumn</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"Range(<parameter>int <replaceable>algusRida</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>algusVeerg</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>lõppRida</replaceable></parameter>, "
"<parameter>int <replaceable>lõppVeerg</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2801
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Constructor. Calling <literal>new Range(<replaceable>startLine</"
"replaceable>, <replaceable>startColumn</replaceable>, <replaceable>endLine</"
"replaceable>, <replaceable>endColumn</replaceable>)</literal> returns the "
"Range from (<replaceable>startLine</replaceable>, <replaceable>startColumn</"
"replaceable>) to (<replaceable>endLine</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>endColumn</replaceable>)."
msgstr ""
"Konstruktor. <literal>new Range(<replaceable>algusRida</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>algusVeerg</replaceable>, <replaceable>lõppRida</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>lõppVeerg</replaceable>)</literal> tagastab vahemiku alates "
"(<replaceable>algusRida</replaceable>, <replaceable>algusVeerg</"
"replaceable>) kuni (<replaceable>lõppRida</replaceable>, "
"<replaceable>lõppVeerg</replaceable>)."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2809
#, no-c-format
msgid "Range(<parameter>Range <replaceable>other</replaceable></parameter>);"
msgstr "Range(<parameter>Range <replaceable>other</replaceable></parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy constructor. Returns a copy of Range <replaceable>other</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Koopia konstruktor. Tagastab vahemiku koopia <replaceable>other</"
"replaceable>."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2817
#, no-c-format
msgid "Range Range.clone();"
msgstr "Range Range.clone();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2818
#, no-c-format
msgid "Returns a clone of the range."
msgstr "Tagastab vahemiku klooni."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2821
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var clone = range.clone();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var clone = range.clone();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2827
#, no-c-format
msgid "bool Range.isEmpty();"
msgstr "bool Range.isEmpty();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2828
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if the start and end cursors are equal."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab <literal>true</literal>, kui nii algus- kui ka lõppkursor on "
"võrdsed."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2831
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var empty = range.isEmpty();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var empty = range.isEmpty();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2840
#, no-c-format
msgid "bool Range.isValid();"
msgstr "bool Range.isValid();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if both start and end cursor are valid, "
"otherwise <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab <literal>true</literal>, kui nii algus- kui ka lõppkursor on "
"korrektsed, vastasel juhul <literal>false</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2844
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: <function>var valid = range.isValid();</function>"
msgstr "Näide: <function>var valid = range.isValid();</function>"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2850
#, no-c-format
msgid "Range Range.invalid();"
msgstr "Range Range.invalid();"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2851
#, no-c-format
msgid "Returns the Range from (-1, -1) to (-1, -1)."
msgstr "Tagastab vahemiku alates (-1, -1) kuni (-1, -1)."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2858
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"bool Range.contains(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>cursor</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"bool Range.contains(<parameter>Cursor <replaceable>kursor</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if this range contains the cursor position, "
"otherwise <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab <literal>true</literal>, kui antud vahemik sisaldab kursori "
"asukohta, vastasel juhul <literal>false</literal>."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2866
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"bool Range.contains(<parameter>Range <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"bool Range.contains(<parameter>Range <replaceable>other</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2867
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if this range contains the Range "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>, otherwise <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tagastab <literal>true</literal>, kui antud vahemik sisaldab vahemikku "
"<replaceable>other</replaceable>, vastasel juhul <literal>false</literal>."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: development.docbook:2875
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"bool Range.containsColumn(<parameter>int <replaceable>column</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"
msgstr ""
"bool Range.containsColumn(<parameter>int <replaceable>veerg</replaceable></"
"parameter>);"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Returns <literal>true</literal>, if <replaceable>column</replaceable> is in "
"the half open interval <literal>[start.column, end.column)</literal>, "
"otherwise <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""
